### 2. Missing Security Headers (OWASP A05)

**Severity: HIGH**

Express ships no security-related HTTP headers by default, leaving the app vulnerable to clickjacking, MIME sniffing, cross-site scripting, and information disclosure (`X-Powered-By: Express`).

**Recommendation:** Add [`helmet`](https://helmetjs.github.io/):

```js
const helmet = require('helmet');

// ✅ Adds 14+ security headers in one line
app.use(helmet());

// X-Powered-By is suppressed, CSP, HSTS, X-Frame-Options, etc. are set
```

